<div class="prose">
	<h3>Beyond LLMs</h3>
	<p>
		Current AI is dominated by autoregressive LLMs — powerful, but fundamentally limited. They predict tokens; they
		don't model the world, reason about causality, or plan ahead. The next wave of systems will need to do all three.
	</p>
	<h3>World models</h3>
	<p>
		A world model lets a system simulate environments, predict outcomes, and plan before acting. Several of Yann LeCun's
		recent papers argue this is the missing ingredient. We think he's right.
	</p>
	<h3>Hyper agents</h3>
	<p>
		Agents that can improve themselves, orchestrate tools autonomously, and run persistent learning loops. Not a chatbot
		wrapper — a genuinely different class of system. We're building infrastructure and ideas around this direction.
	</p>
</div>
<Callout type="note" title="Early days">
